  <prompt>
    <goal>Create docs/standards/INTEGRATION-CONTRACTS.md — interface contracts at every subsystem seam</goal>
    <context>The Spaarke platform has multiple integration seams (BFF↔PCF, BFF↔Graph, BFF↔ServiceBus, PCF↔Dataverse, BFF↔AI Services) but no single document describes the contract at each boundary. Claude needs to know data formats, auth mechanisms, error handling, and retry behavior at each seam to implement cross-layer features correctly.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use /docs-standards skill structure
      - Identify ALL integration seams by reading actual code endpoints and client calls
      - Document each seam's contract: data format, authentication method, error response shape, retry/timeout policy
      - Include request/response examples sourced from actual code — do not fabricate
      - Cross-reference ADRs that constrain each seam (e.g., ADR-008 for auth, ADR-007 for Graph facade)
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
